article.description: Omar Prewitt scored 21 points as William & Mary rolled to a 90-64 win over Delaware on Saturday for its fourth-straight victory.
article.headline: William & Mary rolls to 90-64 win over Delaware
article.linkText: William & Mary rolls to 90-64 win over Delaware
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Omar Prewitt scored 21 points as William & Mary rolled to a 90-64 win over Delaware on Saturday for its fourth-straight victory. Greg Malinowski added 15 points and five rebounds for the Tribe (17-6, 9-3 Colonial Athletic Association) who had a 43-28 rebounding edge over Delaware. Terry Tarpey scored 12 points and led the team with 11 rebounds, Connor Burchfield had 11 points and Sean Sheldon chipped in 10. David Cohn dished 10 assists in addition to scoring seven points. William & Mary led early in the first half and had a 39-22 advantage at the break. Delaware never threatened in the second half and the Tribe rolled to the win. Kory Holden scored 24 points with five rebounds and three assists for the Blue Hens (5-18, 0-12) who have lost 15-straight games. Marvin King-Davis added 22 points and eight rebounds.
